{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d40932da-ea39-4cf5-9c8d-dbe5b7110ad6","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. When you use `dotnet run`, the test host stays alive and watches for code changes, recompiling and re-running tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` spawns a one-shot test execution and exits — it doesn't support the hot reload loop.\n\nSo your workflow is:\n\n```bash\nTESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1 dotnet run\n```\n\n(You already have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled in your project, so you're all set.)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a05f6324-f954-442a-a419-01f472514fd8","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"0C02:3A1531:496396:556455:69F010C9"},"id":"1c009a61-9650-4945-a46e-4a54a054a98b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:43:43.347Z","parentId":"5ae4d123-9b60-4b83-afdd-6923261adedc"}
